The _kattala_ noun pattern: The _kattala_ noun pattern is one of the [[Hebrew noun patterns]] and produces words such as:
| *Shoresh* | *_Pi’el_ verb* | *_Kattala_ Noun* |
|-|-|-|
| בקשׁ <br> seeking | בִּקֵּשׁ<br> _bikeish_ <br> he requested | בַּקָּשָׁה <br> _bakasha_ <br> an instance of eating |
| תקן<br> fixing | תִּקֵּן<br> _tikein_ <br> he fixed | תַּקָּנָה<br> _takkana_ <br> an instituted rule |
| כפר <br> atonement | כִּפֵּר<br> _kipeir_ <br> he granted atonement | כַּפָּרָה <br> _nechama_ <br> an atonement |
The _kattala_ pattern is one of the [[noun patterns that come from _pi’el_ verbs]]. More examples of words in the _ktila_ noun pattern [can be found on Pealim](https://www.pealim.com/dict/?pos=noun&nm=qattala).
